# Testing Strategy - Quick Reference

**For complete details:** `docs/guides/TESTING_GUIDE.md`, `docs/architecture/TESTING_STRATEGY.md`

## 🚨 After Code Changes: Test Review Checklist

**CRITICAL: Never leave failing tests after code changes.**

After any code session with new/modified code, MUST review related tests:

**Pyramid bias:** Prefer **many unit tests** and **fewer** integration/E2E tests; do not duplicate the same assertion at every layer without a clear reason.

1. **Review hierarchy** (bottom to top): unit → integration → e2e
2. **Adjust tests** to match new code behavior (update assertions, mocks, fixtures)
3. **Run tests** at each level and ensure ALL pass before considering work complete
4. **If tests fail, fix them immediately** — don't defer or skip

### Test Review Questions

- Unit tests: Do they cover the changed code paths?
- Integration tests: Do they reflect new behavior correctly?
- E2E tests: Do end-to-end flows still work?
- All tests pass: `make test-unit`, `make test-integration`, `make test-e2e`

If you're unsure which tests are affected, run the full test suite and fix failures.

### GI/KG viewer UI (`web/gi-kg-viewer`) + Playwright

pytest does **not** run browser E2E — use **`make test-ui-e2e`**.

When **viewer UX** changes (labels, routes, layout, theme tokens, accessible names, E2E flows):

1. Update **`web/gi-kg-viewer/e2e/E2E_SURFACE_MAP.md`** if selectors or E2E-visible behavior changed.
2. Update **`e2e/*.spec.ts`** / **`helpers.ts`** / **`fixtures.ts`**; run **`make test-ui-e2e`**.
3. Update **`docs/uxs/UXS-001-gi-kg-viewer.md`** when the **visual or experience contract** changes.

**FastAPI JSON contracts** (new or changed `/api/*` routes): add or extend tests under
**`tests/unit/podcast_scraper/server/`** and **`tests/integration/server/`** (not a root-level
`tests/integration/test_server_api.py`). See **`docs/guides/TESTING_GUIDE.md`** (Browser E2E table).

See **`docs/guides/E2E_TESTING_GUIDE.md`** (section *When you change viewer UX*) and **`.cursorrules`** (*GI/KG viewer UX*).

## 🚨 MANDATORY: Testing Before Commit

**For which tests to run:** Use the **test-scope-decision-tree** skill.

**This project:** See table below for area → command. Run `make docker-test` only when Dockerfile/structure/deps changed.

**Run slow tests ONLY if you changed:**

| Area Changed | Command | Duration |
|--------------|---------|----------|
| Whisper integration (`whisper_integration.py`) | `make test-integration-slow` | ~5-10 min |
| Summarization with ML (`summarizer.py`) | `make test-integration-slow` | ~5-10 min |
| Speaker detection (`speaker_detection.py`) | `make test-integration-slow` | ~5-10 min |
| Full workflow with ML (`workflow.py`) | `make test-all-slow` | ~20-30 min |
| E2E tests with ML models | `make test-e2e-slow` | ~15-20 min |

**When NOT to run slow tests:**

- ❌ Only unit test changes
- ❌ Only documentation changes
- ❌ Only configuration changes (that don't affect ML)
- ❌ Code changes that don't touch ML model paths

### Docker testing (CONDITIONAL)

**Run `make docker-test` ONLY if you changed:**

- ✅ Dockerfile — any changes to build process
- ✅ Project structure — changes to package layout
- ✅ Dependencies — changes to `pyproject.toml` (core deps, metadata)
- ✅ Package configuration — changes to `[tool.setuptools]`

**Skip for:** Python-only changes, docs, tests, non-Docker config.

## ⚡ Test Efficiency Rules

**For the procedure:** Use the **efficient-pytest-runs** skill.

**This project:** Use make targets for suites; for single-test debug use pytest with `-v --tb=short -ra -rs`. Never run the same suite twice.

## Pytest Markers

### Use These Markers

```python
@pytest.mark.slow              # Tests that take >5s
@pytest.mark.integration       # Tests that use multiple modules
@pytest.mark.e2e              # End-to-end tests with full workflow
@pytest.mark.ml_models        # Tests that load ML models
@pytest.mark.critical_path    # Fast tests that run on PRs
```

### Marker Combinations

```python
# Slow integration test with ML models
@pytest.mark.slow
@pytest.mark.integration
@pytest.mark.ml_models
def test_whisper_transcription():
    pass

# Fast critical path E2E test
@pytest.mark.e2e
@pytest.mark.critical_path
def test_workflow_download_only():
    pass
```

## Test Structure

### Test Naming Convention

```python
# Good - descriptive scenario
def test_fetch_url_retries_on_connection_error():
    pass

def test_sanitize_filename_replaces_invalid_chars():
    pass

# Bad - not descriptive
def test_fetch_url():
    pass

def test_sanitize():
    pass
```

### Unit tests and `pyproject` extras (mandatory for authors)

- **`tests/unit/`** must **not** require **`[ml]`**, **`[llm]`**, or **`[compare]`** — mock, stub
  `sys.modules`, or move to **`tests/integration/`**.
- **`[dev]`** is the baseline (see `pyproject.toml`); **`check_unit_test_imports.py`** guards ML
  import-time issues (it does not install **`[server]`**).
- **Viewer / FastAPI:** CI **`test-unit`** installs **`pip install -e .[dev]`** only. Module-level
  **`pytest.importorskip("fastapi")`** skips viewer HTTP tests without **`[server]`**; install
  **`.[server]`** locally to run them. Avoid real FAISS / torch / spacy in unit tests — use patches
  (see `docs/guides/UNIT_TESTING_GUIDE.md` § *Pyproject extras*).
- **Local CI parity:** **`make venv-dev-init`** + **`make test-unit-dev-venv`** uses a separate
  **`.venv-dev`** (`.[dev]` only) so you do not strip extras from the main **`.venv`**.

### Test Organization

**Unit** mirrors the source tree. **Integration** is organized by domain subsystem.
**E2E** is flat by user scenario.

```text
tests/
├── unit/              # Mirrors src/ tree; no [ml]/[llm] extras
│   └── podcast_scraper/
│       ├── providers/ml/test_nli_loader.py
│       └── ...
├── integration/       # By domain subsystem (not source module)
│   ├── providers/     # factories, protocols, llm/, ml/, ollama/
│   ├── workflow/      # orchestration, stages, metadata, resume
│   ├── gi/            # GI/KG artifacts, evidence stack
│   ├── server/        # FastAPI viewer API (e.g. test_server_api, corpus_library, index_rebuild)
│   ├── search/        # FAISS indexing
│   ├── rss/           # RSS parsing, HTTP fetching
│   └── test_*.py      # cross-cutting (filesystem, retry, cache)
└── e2e/              # End-to-end workflow tests
    ├── test_workflow_basic.py
    └── test_workflow_full.py
```

See `docs/guides/INTEGRATION_TESTING_GUIDE.md` § Directory Organization for details.

## Mocking Requirements

### Always Mock External Dependencies

```python
from unittest.mock import Mock, patch

# Mock HTTP calls
@patch("podcast_scraper.downloader.requests.Session")
def test_download(mock_session):
    mock_session.get.return_value = Mock(status_code=200, content=b"data")
    # test code

# Mock Whisper
@patch("podcast_scraper.whisper_integration.whisper")
def test_transcribe(mock_whisper):
    mock_whisper.load_model.return_value = Mock()
    # test code

# Mock file I/O (use tempfile)
import tempfile
def test_save_file():
    with tempfile.TemporaryDirectory() as tmpdir:
        # test code
```

### What to Mock

- ✅ HTTP requests (`requests.Session`, `requests.get`)
- ✅ Whisper models (`whisper.load_model`, `whisper.transcribe`)
- ✅ File I/O (use `tempfile.TemporaryDirectory`)
- ✅ spaCy models (mock NER extraction)
- ✅ Time operations (`time.sleep`, `time.time`)
- ✅ OpenAI API calls (when implemented)

## Coverage Requirements

- **Target:** >80% line coverage
- **Focus:** Core business logic (not mocks/fixtures)
- **Check:** `make coverage` generates HTML report in `htmlcov/`

## Running Tests

### Common Commands

```bash
# Fast tests (default for development)
make ci-fast               # No coverage, fastest (~6-10 min)

# Individual test suites
make test-unit            # Unit tests only (~2-5 min)
make test-integration     # All integration tests (~10-15 min)
make test-e2e            # All E2E tests (~20-30 min)

# Slow tests (when needed)
make test-integration-slow  # Slow integration (~5-10 min)
make test-e2e-slow         # Slow E2E (~15-20 min)
make test-all-slow         # All slow tests (~20-30 min)

# Full CI validation
make ci                   # All checks + tests + coverage (~10-15 min)

# Debug specific test
pytest tests/unit/test_config.py::test_config_validation -v -s
pytest -k "test_whisper" -v  # Run tests matching pattern
```

### Parallel Execution

- Tests run in parallel by default (`-n auto`)
- Disable for debugging: `pytest -n 0 -v -s`

## Quick Decision Tree

```text
Changed code?
├─ Docs only? → No tests needed
├─ Unit tests only? → make ci-fast
├─ ML code changed?
│  ├─ Integration ML? → make ci-fast + make test-integration-slow
│  ├─ E2E ML? → make ci-fast + make test-e2e-slow
│  └─ Both? → make ci-fast + make test-all-slow
├─ Dockerfile/structure? → make ci-fast + make docker-test
└─ No ML? → make ci-fast
```

## Remember

1. **Start with fast tests** — catches most issues quickly
2. **Run slow tests conditionally** — only when touching ML code
3. **Mock external dependencies** — tests must be isolated
4. **Use descriptive test names** — `test_<function>_<scenario>`
5. **Target >80% coverage** — focus on business logic
6. **Never run the same test suite twice** — collect all info in one run
7. **Fix failing tests immediately** — never leave tests broken

